comments: Lively II (DAL) firms up in a screening position in Dort's (OKC) path.
Doncic (DAL) places part of his hand underneath the ball prior to resuming his dribble.
Dort (OKC) legally contests the jump shot attempt by Doncic (DAL) and any marginal contact is created by Doncic extending his leg.
Irving (DAL) lifts his arm upwards into Gilgeous-Alexander's (OKC) arm, but the contact does not affect his SQBR.
Dort (OKC) and Doncic (DAL) mutually come together at the same spot with their hands on the ball and the contact is incidental.
Although both Dort (OKC) and Doncic (DAL) have their hands on the ball, the ball becomes loose when both players return to the floor and play should not have been stopped for a held ball.
Dort (OKC) has an arm extended towards Doncic (DAL) and Doncic lifts his own arm upwards into it to create the contact.
Joe (OKC) is retracting his arm into a vertical position and the contact with Washington's (DAL) arm is incidental.  Any contact by Gilgeous-Alexander (OKC) is marginal.
Holmgren (OKC) briefly grasps Jones Jr.'s (DAL) arm before he pursues the loose ball and gains possession.
Williams (OKC) steps into Irving (DAL) on the perimeter but the contact does not affect his SQBR.
Williams (OKC) legally contests Irving's (DAL) driving shot attempt.
Gilgeous-Alexander (OKC) extends his elbow and initiates contact with Doncic's (DAL) head/face during the driving shot attempt.
Williams (OKC) is the last player to touch the ball before it is out of bounds.
Doncic (DAL) and Dort (OKC) mutually engage during the throw-in and Dort is not dislodged from his position when Doncic releases.

As Doncic (DAL) attempts to split the defenders, Holmgren (OKC) makes clean contact with the ball causing Doncic to bobble it.  Gilgeous-Alexander (OKC) then reaches in and makes clean contact with the ball to dislodge it from Doncic's possession.
Irving (DAL) initiates contact with Holmgren's (OKC) arm, which affects his shot attempt near the rim.
Dort (OKC) commits a take foul on Doncic (DAL).
